  <mads:note type="source">Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 2 , 1867, p. 1154: "Neophron, 
    or Neophon, of Sicyon, a tragic writer of doubtful age....in the Scholia to the Medea of Euripides we have two fragments 
    of a play written by him on the same subject.....Besides these we have fifteen lines quoted by Stobaeus, from the
    same tragedy..."
   </mads:note>  
  <mads:note type="source">  Brill's New Pauly: "Neophron, of Sicyon. Tragedian, 2nd half of 5th cent. BC
    according to the Suda (TrGF I 15 T 1) the author of 120 plays, and the first to depict tutors and the 
    torture of slaves on the stage....".  Zimmermann, Bernhard (Freiburg). "Neophron." Brill's New Pauly. 
    Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2008. Brill Online.</mads:note>
